Description: Fragment of flattened handle from a Knidian pottery transport amphora. Clay medium red-brown; mixed inclusions, some large. Rectangular stamp at top of handle with Greek inscription and anchor symbol.
Type series: KT724 (Virginia Grace's unpublished K(nidian) T(ype) series)
Curator's comments: Names Agathokles and Theudosios' Trimmed. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.116, 2
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0311)
